# Aria v2 — Project Conventions

Read [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](../../ARCHITECTURE.md), [`wiring.md`](../../wiring.md),
and [`ABSENCES.md`](../../ABSENCES.md) for the map and the things that must stay
gone. This file is the short version of the rules that hold across the codebase.

## Roles do not blur

- **Claude conducts.** It owns the conversation's content: intent, which loop,
  what to ask, whether the plan is right. It is the brain in the conversation,
  not a tool called after a dumb router already decided. (This is the v1 defect,
  inverted — never reintroduce a non-reasoning front door that decides intent.)
- **The voice layer renders.** A fast transport (LiveKit + a fast model) is ears
  and mouth — STT, TTS, turn-taking, barge-in. It never decides anything.
- **Claude Code builds.** One engine (the Agent SDK, a managed `claude`
  subprocess) does every kind of work. There is no Cursor.

A change that asks the voice layer to decide intent, or adds a second engine, is
a regression.

## Capability is data, the core is thin

New capability is a **loop file** (`loops/*.yaml`) or an **endpoint**, never a
new branch of the conductor. If you're editing `src/conductor.py` to add a
feature, stop — it belongs in a loop.

## One brain, many transports

The conductor-driving logic and the **mechanical go-gate** live once, in
`src/brain.py::AriaBrain`. Text and voice are thin transports over it. Nothing
dispatches without a confirmed plan and an explicit go — enforced in code, not
by prompting.

## Failures are loud; verify against ground truth

No silent fallbacks, no `try/except: pass`, no fabricated success, never blame a
third party. "Done" for code is tests pass + a diff exists + it builds + an
honest outcome-log row — checked by the dispatcher against git/test ground
truth, never the engine's narration. A broken verifier reads as `unverified`
(a loud non-pass), never as success.

## Doctrine has one home and must reach the engine

`prompts/_principles.md` is the single home of the engineering doctrine, injected
by `{{include:_principles}}` into the conductor persona AND the engine
instruction. These `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` govern the build-time IDE agent only —
they are inert to Aria's runtime engine, so never rely on them to reach it.

## Cost & secrets are mechanical

Models, caps, and the billing path live in `src/config.py` (from `.env`);
nothing else reads the environment. Secret fields are `repr=False`. Pin only
verified-live model ids; `src/preflight.py` asserts each resolves at boot.

## Don't substitute models or keep legacy

The conductor reasons on Opus (`claude-opus-4-8`); a fast tier may serve routine
turns once verified. No back-compat, no style variants, no dead paths — when a
collapse makes something gone, record it in `ABSENCES.md` so it stays gone.
